On July 9 1968 Chamberlain was the centerpiece of a major trade between the 76ers and the Los Angeles Lakers who sent center Darrall Imhoff ( the unfortunate ex - Knicks center who started against Chamberlain when the latter scored 100 points ) forward Jerry Chambers and guard Archie Clark to Philadelphia making it the first time a reigning NBA Most Valuable Player was traded the next season .
